《'''论摩擦激起的热源'''》<ref name=":0">{{cite book |author1=胡承正 |editor=吉正霞 |title=热力学与统计物理学 |date=2009-06 |publisher=科学出版社 |location=北京 |isbn=9787030246042 |page=1-2 |edition=第一版 |url=http://www.ecsponline.com/yz/B4481F647F70242D8AC43A7886AB2F86B000.pdf |accessdate=2020-07-24 |archive-date=2020-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724043651/http://www.ecsponline.com/yz/B4481F647F70242D8AC43A7886AB2F86B000.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>（{{lang-en|An Experimental Enquiry Concerning the Source of the Heat which is Excited by Friction}}<ref name="origin">Benjamin Count of Rumford (1798) [https://books.google.com/books?id=6lBFAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA80#v=onepage&q&f=false "An inquiry concerning the source of the heat which is excited by friction,"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6lBFAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA80#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200811213837 }} ''Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London'', '''88''' :   80–102. {{doi|10.1098/rstl.1798.0006}}</ref>，也称为伦福德的炮筒镗孔摩擦生热实验<ref name="Abstract">{{cite journal |author1=刘德磊、曾莉莉、屈志伟 |title=经典热力学发展概述 |journal=《广州化工》 |date=2012年 |issue=2 |pages=26-28 |url=http://www.cqvip.com/qk/93773x/2012002/40564629.html |accessdate=2020-07-24 |archive-date=2020-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724040711/http://www.cqvip.com/qk/93773x/2012002/40564629.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>）（1798），是由[[本杰明·汤普森，伦福德伯爵|伦福德]]最早发表在《[[自然科学会报|自然科学会报]]》<ref name="JD" /> 上的一篇论文，这篇论文向当时的热质理论抛出了一个重大难题，并引发了19世纪的[[热力学|热力学]]革命。

==背景==
{{main|热质说}}
[[热质说|热质说]]是一种曾用来解释热的物理现象的理论。此理论认为热是一种称为“热质”（caloric）的流体物质，热质会由温度高的物体流到温度低的物体，也可以穿过固体或液体的孔隙中。

伦福德是[[热质说|热质说]]的反对者，他在当时经过研究后认为，所有的[[气体|气体]]和[[液体|液体]]都是绝对不[[热传导|导热]]的。由于他的观点过于超前，不被当时的科学界认可，并遭到[[约翰·道尔顿|约翰·道尔顿]]<ref name="JD">{{cite book | author=Cardwell, D.S.L. | title=From Watt to Clausius: The Rise of Thermodynamics in the Early Industrial Age | location=Heinemann | publisher=London | year=1971 | isbn=0-435-54150-1 |page=99-102}}</ref>和[[约翰·莱斯利|约翰·莱斯利]]<ref>{{cite book | author=Leslie, J. | title=An Experimental Enquiry into the Nature and Propagation of Heat | publisher=London | year=1804 | id=}}</ref>等人的批评。

由于伦福德受天主教的[[目的論論證|目的論論證]]<ref>Rumford (1804) "[http://rstl.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/94/77.full.pdf+html An enquiry concerning the nature of heat and the mode of its communication] {{Wayback|url=http://rstl.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/94/77.full.pdf+html |date=20180528210831 }}" ''Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society'' ''p.''77</ref>影响很深，他可能希望授予水某种特殊的导热权<ref name="JD" />。

尽管伦福德试图将热量与[[運動_(物理學)|運動]]建立联系，不过没有证据表明他研究过[[分子运动论|分子运动论]]或是[[活力|活力]]理论。

在这篇论文中，伦福德承认他曾认为热是运动过程的一部分<ref>From p. 100 of Rumford's paper of 1798:  "Before I finish this paper, I would beg leave to observe, that although, in treating the subject I have endeavoured to investigate, I have made no mention of the names of those who have gone over the same ground before me, nor of the success of their labours; this omission has not been owing to any want of respect for my predecessors, but was merely to avoid prolixity, and to be more at liberty to pursue, without interruption, the natural train of my own ideas." </ref>。这与[[弗兰西斯·培根|弗兰西斯·培根]]<ref>In his ''Novum Organum'' (1620), Francis Bacon concludes that heat is the motion of the particles composing matter.  In Francis Bacon, ''Novum Organum'' (London, England:  William Pickering, 1850), from [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=174 page 164:] {{Wayback|url=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=174 |date=20200818110012 }}  " … Heat appears to be Motion."  [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=175 From p. 165:] {{Wayback|url=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=175 |date=20200731224346 }}  " … the very essence of Heat, or the ''Substantial self'' of Heat,  is motion and nothing else, … "  [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=178 From p. 168:] {{Wayback|url=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=nyp.33433087528570;view=1up;seq=178 |date=20200727075919 }}  " … Heat is not a uniform Expansive Motion of the whole, but of the small particles of the body; … "</ref>、[[罗伯特·波义耳|罗伯特·波义耳]]<ref>"Of the mechanical origin of heat and cold" in:  Robert Boyle, ''Experiments, Notes, &c. About the Mechanical Origine or Production of Divers Particular Qualities:'' … (London, England:  E. Flesher (printer), 1675).  At the conclusion of Experiment VI, Boyle notes that if a nail is driven completely into a piece of wood, then further blows with the hammer cause it to become hot as the hammer's force is transformed into random motion of the nail's atoms.  [https://archive.org/stream/experimentsnotes00boyl#page/n99/mode/2up From pp. 61-62:]   " … the impulse given by the stroke, being unable either to drive the nail further on, or destroy its interness [i.e., entireness, integrity], must be spent in making various vehement and intestine commotion of the parts among themselves, and in such an one we formerly observed the nature of heat to consist."</ref>、[[罗伯特·胡克|罗伯特·胡克]]<ref>"Lectures of Light" (May 1681) in:  Robert Hooke with R. Waller, ed., ''The Posthumous Works of Robert Hooke'' … (London, England:  Samuel Smith and Benjamin Walford, 1705).  [https://books.google.com/books?id=6xVTAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA116#v=onepage&q&f=false From page 116:] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6xVTAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA116#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200812162322 }}  "Now Heat, as I shall afterward prove, is nothing but the internal Motion of the Particles of [a] Body; and the hotter a Body is, the more violently are the Particles moved, … "</ref>、[[约翰·洛克|约翰·洛克]]<ref>Sometime during the period 1698-1704, John Locke wrote his book ''Elements of Natural Philosophy'', which was first published in 1720:  John Locke with Pierre Des Maizeaux, ed., ''A Collection of Several Pieces of Mr. John Locke, Never Before Printed, Or Not Extant in His Works'' (London, England:  R. Francklin, 1720).  [https://books.google.com/books?id=QqxsP-VKrpkC&pg=PA224#v=onepage&q&f=false From p. 224:] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QqxsP-VKrpkC&pg=PA224#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200724082023 }}  "''Heat'', is a very brisk agitation of the insensible parts of the object, which produces in us that sensation, from whence we denominate the object ''hot'': so what in our sensation is heat, in the object is nothing but motion.  This appears by the way, whereby heat is produc'd:  for we see that the rubbing of a brass-nail upon a board, will make it very hot; and the axle-trees of carts and coaches are often hot, and sometimes to a degree, that it sets them on fire, by rubbing of the nave of the wheel upon it."</ref>和[[亨利·卡文迪什|亨利·卡文迪什]]<ref>Henry Cavendish (1783) "Observations on Mr. Hutchins's experiments for determining the degree of cold at which quicksilver freezes," ''Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London'',  '''73''' : 303-328.  [https://books.google.com/books?id=AE9FAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA1-PA313#v=onepage&q&f=false From the footnote continued on p. 313:] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AE9FAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA1-PA313#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200811213840 }}  " … I think Sir Isaac Newton's opinion, that heat consists in the internal motion of the particles of bodies, much the most probable … "</ref>过去的一些观点不谋而合。

==实验==
伦福德观察了[[慕尼黑|慕尼黑]][[兵工廠|兵工廠]][[加农炮|加农炮]]{{tsl|en|Boring (manufacturing)|镗孔 (制造)|镗孔}}過程中[[摩擦力|摩擦]]生热的一些过程后进行了这个实验。他将一个加农炮筒浸入水中，并准备了一种特别钝的镗钻机。在这种情况下他不断的用钻机摩擦炮筒，钻出大量高热量的碎屑，并发现大概两个半小时后水[[沸腾|沸腾]]了<ref name=":0" /><ref name="origin" />。但问题在于，通过比较炮筒的[[比热容|比热容]]可以发现，这个过程中炮筒并没有损失能将水加热水平质量的物质来加热水，这与热质说的结论不符。

伦福德认为，看似无限的热量生成与热质理论不吻合。他认为在这个过程中唯一进行的操作只是运动和摩擦，因此他认为热不可能是物质而有可能是运动。

伦福德甚至粗略估计出产生1开尔文的热需要5.5焦耳的机械能，但他并未尝试进一步量化所产生的热量或测量[[热功当量|热量的机械当量]]<ref name="Abstract" />。

==影响==
[[Image:Joule's_Apparatus_(Harper's_Scan).png|thumb]]的仪器]]
大多数当时的科学家认为热质说的确存在不完善之处，可以通过进一步完善该理论来适应该实验的结果，这一派科学家包括[[威廉·亨利|威廉·亨利]]<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Henry |first1=William |title=A review of some experiments which have been supposed to disprove the materiality of heat |journal={{tsl|en|Manchester Memoirs|曼彻斯特回忆录|Manchester Memoirs}} |date=1802 |issue=V |page=603 }}</ref>和{{tsl|en|Thomas Thomson (chemist)|托马斯·汤普森 (化学家)|托马斯·汤普森}}。此外，汤普森<ref>{{tsl|en|Thomas Thomson (chemist)|托马斯·汤普森 (化学家)|Thomson, T.}} "Caloric", Supplement on Chemistry, ''[[大英百科全书|Encyclopædia Britannica]]'', 3rd ed.</ref>、[[永斯·贝采利乌斯|永斯·贝采利乌斯]]和{{tsl|en|Antoine César Becquerel|安东尼·塞瑟}}发现了[[電|電]]似乎也能由摩擦“无限产生”。在当时没有一个科学家愿意承认电不是一种流体。

最终，伦福德声称的“无限生成”的热量被认为是该研究的鲁莽[[外推|外推]]。{{tsl|en|Charles Haldat|查尔斯·海尔戴特}}批评，伦福德的实验{{tsl|en|reproducibility|可重复性}}十分差<ref>Haldat, C.N.A (1810) "Inquiries concerning the heat produced by friction", ''Journal de Physique'' lxv, ''p.''213</ref>，整个实验看起来有一些偏见<ref name="JD" />。

然而，伦福德的实验给了[[詹姆斯·普雷斯科特·焦耳|焦耳]]灵感，1840年代焦耳再次精确的做了一次本实验，这次他用上了测定热量的仪器，最终在热质说的基础上建立了分子运动论这门科学。

